    <name>
      <text>Cubic_1</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>Determine a complex root of the cubic equation \[ {@simpcubic@} = 0.\] Hint: the answer should be given in the form \(p + qi\). <br /> [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>Firstly, look for a real root by dividing the equation by \({@x-a@}\) where \(a\) is a factor of the constant {@constcoeff@}.</p>
<p>In this case \(a = {@n1@}\) is the appropriate value.</p>
<p>Hence dividing {@simpcubic=0@} by {@x-n1@} gives \[{@simpquadratic[1]=0@}\] Using the quadratic formula \[x=\frac{-b±\sqrt{b^2-4ac}}{2a}\] for the equation \(ax^2+bx+c\) gives \[x= \frac{{@-bcoeff@}±{@sqrt(bcoeff^2-4*acoeff*ccoeff)@}}{@2*acoeff@}\]</p>
<p>Therefore \( x = {@z1@},{@z2@}\)</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
    <defaultgrade>1</defaultgrade>
    <penalty>0</penalty>
